  carbohydrates: 79 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 49 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 910 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/greek-diner-spaghetti-with-chicken-67d12e569871c5f9ae2c0fab
time required: 25 minutes
servings: 2
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Mince @dill{1/4%ounce}. Dice @tomato{1%unit} into 1/2-inch pieces. Quarter @lemon{1%unit}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

While pasta cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic, scallion whites, @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until fragrant and slightly softened, ~{1%minute}.

Reduce heat to medium; stir in @veggie stock concentrate{2%unit}, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, half the dill, half the @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and 1/4 cup pasta cooking water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). (Ladle straight from the pot if pasta hasn't finished cooking yet.) Cook, stirring and smashing feta with the back of a spoon or spatula, until sauce is creamy and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in tomato and @spinach{5%ounce} (add in batches if necessary). Cook, stirring, until tomato is softened and spinach is wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

> Use a second large pan here.

To pan with sauce, stir in spaghetti, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and as much remaining dill as you like; toss until thoroughly coated.

> If needed, add another drizzle of olive oil and more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}; top with scallion greens and remaining feta. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Slice chicken crosswise. Serve atop pasta.